      • phi

        public static int phi(float m,
                      int n)
        Calculates the number of positive integers that are less than m and are not divisible by any of the first n primes. Uses recursive relation
        phi(m,n) = phi(m,n-1) - phi(floor(m/p_n),n-1)
        Parameters:
        m -
        n -
        Returns:

        public static BigInteger phi(BigDecimal m,

        public static int pi(float m)
